Godwin Isenyo, Kaduna A Naval Commodore based in Jaji, near Kaduna, has been murdered. It was learnt that the senior officer was murdered by yet-to-be-identified men who dumped her corpse in a well in a village near the military cantonment. It was gathered that the officer was last seen in Jaji on September 13, 2019, and was working at the Command Secondary School, Jaji. As of the time of filing this report, the circumstances surrounding her murder was still sketchy. A source told our correspondent that the authorities of the military in Jaji had placed some of her close staff and family members under close watch. He added that two persons had been arrested in Zaria when they attempted to dispose of the deceased’s car. “The two suspects confessed to have taken part in the murder of the senior military officer. They later led investigators to Agwanloyo, to an abandoned shallow well near the Deeper life Church in Jaji cantonment. “The corpse had been dismembered and put in a Ghana-must-go bag before being dumped in the shallow well.” READ ALSO: Victim identifies suspected rapist, who stole her pants Calls to the Public Relations Office of the Armed Forces Command and Staff College went unanswered and there was no reply to a text message sent to his phone. Similar calls to the state Police Public Relations Officer, Yakubu Sabo, were also unanswered. Copyright PUNCH.
